01:22:28.220 --> 01:22:29.660
I think perhaps here you're talking

01:22:29.660 --> 01:22:33.380
about databases and
this sort of thing.

01:22:33.380 --> 01:22:34.680
All right.

01:22:34.680 --> 01:22:38.700
No, I guess we're trying
to encourage countries

01:22:38.700 --> 01:22:42.770
to make their geographical
names data available for free.

01:22:42.770 --> 01:22:45.380
But, as you know, this is
not the case particularly

01:22:45.380 --> 01:22:46.690
for many countries in Europe.

01:22:46.690 --> 01:22:50.280
These names are not
available for free as a group.

01:22:50.280 --> 01:22:53.290
Some countries have moved in
this direction, though Finland,

01:22:53.290 --> 01:22:58.210 position:56%
for example, now has its names data
and other topographic data available

01:22:58.210 --> 01:23:00.730
to the public without charge.

01:23:00.730 --> 01:23:05.000
There are other issues, of
course, of ownership of names.

01:23:05.000 --> 01:23:08.880
This does come up with
indigenous or aboriginal names,

01:23:08.880 --> 01:23:14.980
and really whether these
names belong to the Earth

01:23:14.980 --> 01:23:18.540 position:56%
and to the people, whether
everybody has access to these names.

01:23:18.540 --> 01:23:21.010
There are many interesting
