03:22:04.390 --> 03:22:08.160
and got everybody together in one
place and it had taken two days.

03:22:08.160 --> 03:22:09.850
Document success.

03:22:09.850 --> 03:22:13.190 position:56%
One thing you can do is if you've
got a best practice, well, you know,

03:22:13.190 --> 03:22:16.830
you could pay somebody to put
together a best practices document.

03:22:16.830 --> 03:22:19.640
Target specialist communities,
and I'll get back to this again,

03:22:19.640 --> 03:22:21.430
that have an interest
in the resulting data.

03:22:21.430 --> 03:22:24.510
These are Type I, Type II,
and Type III volunteers.

03:22:24.510 --> 03:22:28.020
And accept the idea, and
this is real important one,

03:22:28.020 --> 03:22:31.950 position:56%
that the idea of going beyond your
mission can be a valuable motivator.

03:22:31.950 --> 03:22:35.980
BGN's requirements
are pretty strict.

03:22:35.980 --> 03:22:38.700
And hopefully I'll give
you a way of looking at it

03:22:38.700 --> 03:22:42.490
where maybe you can think about
it a little differently and kind

03:22:42.490 --> 03:22:45.770
of go beyond that --
those boundaries.

03:22:45.770 --> 03:22:48.100
All right.

03:22:48.100 --> 03:22:49.400
Quality Assurance.

03:22:49.400 --> 03:22:52.450
There's a misconception crowd
source data is unreliable.

