04:01:11.200 --> 04:01:16.040
So in keeping with John Hyde's
comments in the December 1899 issue

04:01:16.040 --> 04:01:19.490
of National Geographic, the Society
has always regarded the U.S. Board

04:01:19.490 --> 04:01:24.020 position:56%
on Geographic Names as the authority
on geographic nomenclature.

04:01:24.020 --> 04:01:28.100
A fact that is duly addressed
in the Geographic Style Manual,

04:01:28.100 --> 04:01:31.290
